'''Molsberg''' ([[English language|English]]: ''Mols hill'') is a [[Hamlet (place)|hamlet]] in the southeastern [[Netherlands]]. It is located close to the village of [[Simpelveld]] in the municipality of [[Simpelveld]], [[Limburg, Netherlands|Limburg]], about 20&nbsp;km east of [[Maastricht]]. The village has a population of 300 people after it was expanded with 54 new houses in 2004.

The name Molsberg refers to the hill (berg) it is built on and to the Mols family.<ref>[http://www.toeristischsimpelveld.nl/online/media/pdf/beschrijving_Simpelveld.pdf Tourism information Simpelveld] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504105023/http://www.toeristischsimpelveld.nl/online/media/pdf/beschrijving_Simpelveld.pdf |date=2014-05-04 }}</ref> Molsberg is also the name of the hill the village is built on. This hill goes up to 212m with an average incline of 4% and is part of the [[Amstel Gold Race]].

The farm located at Molsberg 96 dates from 1732 and has been designated a [[rijksmonument|national monument]].<ref>[http://monumentenregister.cultureelerfgoed.nl/php/main.php?cAction=search&sCompMonNr=33616 Molsberg 96] on the Dutch monument register</ref>

